## Serverless Architecture

This project uses a serverless / FaaS architecture.

### Function design

- Keep functions small and focused: one event trigger, one responsibility
- Minimize cold start time: lazy-initialize heavy dependencies outside the handler
- Avoid shared mutable state between invocations; treat each invocation as stateless
- Use environment variables for configuration; never hardcode service endpoints or secrets

### Error handling

- Always return structured errors with HTTP status codes for API triggers
- Use dead-letter queues (DLQ) for async event handlers
- Log with structured JSON including the event source and invocation ID

### Observability

- Use distributed tracing to correlate logs across function invocations
- Set appropriate timeouts and memory limits per function based on measured usage
